/favicon.png","site-lib/fonts/70cc7ff27245e82ad414.ttf","site-lib/fonts/454577c22304619db035.ttf","site-lib/fonts/52ac8f3034507f1d9e53.ttf","site-lib/fonts/05b618077343fbbd92b7.ttf","site-lib/fonts/4bb6ac751d1c5478ff3a.woff2","site-lib/fonts/c504db5c06caaf7cdfba.woff2","site-lib/fonts/01dcbad1bac635f9c9cd.woff2","site-lib/media/6155340132a851f6089e.svg","site-lib/media/2308ab1944a6bfa5c5b8.svg","site-lib/html/file-tree-content.html","site-lib/scripts/webpage.js","site-lib/styles/snippets.css","site-lib/styles/obsidian.css","site-lib/styles/theme.css","site-lib/styles/global-variable-styles.css","site-lib/styles/main-styles.css"],"webpages":{"06-newsletter/2026-week26.html":{"title":"2026-week26","icon":"","description":"A curation of ideas, memes and media which would which would have cluttered the chat too much.Now a lot of things might seem irrelevant or out of them blue, that's cause I'm gonna be sending it to several people.\nI'm planning to do this instead of being constantly active on whatsapp/insta.\nIf you have not interacted with a particular piece of media, beware of potential spoilers.I wanted to include my rant about how both sides of communism and capitalism debate and my annoyances with them in here, but it turned out to be waaay too long. I will be writing a blog post on it probably.\nI will be finished with it after I am done doing a 100% run of papers, please.\n<img alt=\"4h0364qnzn8h1.jpeg\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/4h0364qnzn8h1.jpeg\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 200px; max-width: 100%;\">let's get onto it.Tadc ended. It was great show which deserved a better ending in my opinion, but these types of endings are what fuel really good fanfics.<br>\n<img alt=\"Pasted image 20260627193700.png\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/pasted-image-20260627193700.png\" target=\"_self\">\nAn obligatory \"fuck you\" to gooseworx. No way it had been planned since 2016 😭.throw in the dysfunctional canon family in the wild and you're gonna get ratioed by wholesome fanfics and fanarts.<br>\n<img alt=\"HEzae_QacAEwCMe.png\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/hezae_qacaewcme.png\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 500px; max-width: 100%;\"><br><img alt=\"Gv5-uJwXUAAOxoz.jpg\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/gv5-ujwxuaaoxoz.jpg\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 300px; max-width: 100%;\"><br><img alt=\"HK3hduDagAAaoGI.jpg\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/hk3hdudagaaaogi.jpg\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 300px; max-width: 100%;\"><br>\n<img alt=\"8xfim00w8d6h1.jpeg\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/8xfim00w8d6h1.jpeg\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 300px; max-width: 100%;\"><br><img alt=\"ytz2ubdj8w8h1.png\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/ytz2ubdj8w8h1.png\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 300px; max-width: 100%;\">\nRadical centrist stalin<br><img alt=\"HJMbXLeWwAA-etT.jpg\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/hjmbxlewwaa-ett.jpg\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 400px; max-width: 100%;\">\nclassic horseshoe. <br><img alt=\"HH3vbR8aoAAG-ka.jpg\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/hh3vbr8aoaag-ka.jpg\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 400px; max-width: 100%;\">\nThis one had been pretty popular.\nNot sure about the other quadrants, but going with the common libright theory, as long as the state stays out of it, unions are not a problem. The main issue is when you have state mandated unions which cause issues.\nI have not found people with the given \"opposite\" beliefs yet. I'll let you interpret this one on your own lol.<br>\n<img alt=\"h0d1vl8wyn8h1.jpeg\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/h0d1vl8wyn8h1.jpeg\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 300px; max-width: 100%;\">Saw someone describe themselves as neurospicy, and now I can't not think of that whenever I think about neurodivergence.<br><img alt=\"Pasted image 20260627193833.png\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/pasted-image-20260627193833.png\" target=\"_self\">\nClassic reddit moment. The top two posts. <br><img alt=\"Pasted image 20260627194037.png\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/pasted-image-20260627194037.png\" target=\"_self\">\n🙂<br><img alt=\"1unp0g930dsg1.jpeg\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/1unp0g930dsg1.jpeg\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 400px; max-width: 100%;\">\nThis is blatant misinformation. My socks are actually longer than shown in the figure. (/s obviously 😭)\nI can cook paneer relatively consistently, and I seem to be happy with the results. the pic below of an unfinished attempt is the only one I could find.<br>\n<img alt=\"Pasted image 20260627194214.png\" src=\"06-newsletter/attachments/pasted-image-20260627194214.png\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 600px; max-width: 100%;\">My ps1 internship station has not contacted in more than a week now. Atp, as long as I get free marks I do not care.This was a kind of a pilot thingy which I am sending to people who may potentially like this stuff. I may send this every week.","aliases":[],"inlineTags":[],"frontmatterTags":[],"headers":[{"heading":"Media","level":1,"id":"Media_0"},{"heading":"Tadc","level":2,"id":"Tadc_0"},{"heading":"tcoaal.","level":2,"id":"tcoaal._0"},{"heading":"ddlc","level":2,"id":"ddlc_0"},{"heading":"political stuff","level":1,"id":"political_stuff_0"},{"heading":"misc","level":1,"id":"misc_0"},{"heading":"life updates","level":1,"id":"life_updates_0"}],"links":[],"author":"","coverImageURL":".","fullURL":"06-newsletter/2026-week26.html","pathToRoot":"..","attachments":["06-newsletter/attachments/4h0364qnzn8h1.jpeg","06-newsletter/attachments/pasted-image-20260627193700.png","06-newsletter/attachments/hezae_qacaewcme.png","06-newsletter/attachments/gv5-ujwxuaaoxoz.jpg","06-newsletter/attachments/hk3hdudagaaaogi.jpg","06-newsletter/attachments/8xfim00w8d6h1.jpeg","06-newsletter/attachments/ytz2ubdj8w8h1.png","06-newsletter/attachments/hjmbxlewwaa-ett.jpg","06-newsletter/attachments/hh3vbr8aoaag-ka.jpg","06-newsletter/attachments/h0d1vl8wyn8h1.jpeg","06-newsletter/attachments/pasted-image-20260627193833.png","06-newsletter/attachments/pasted-image-20260627194037.png","06-newsletter/attachments/1unp0g930dsg1.jpeg","06-newsletter/attachments/pasted-image-20260627194214.png"],"createdTime":1782567847967,"modifiedTime":1782576112212,"sourceSize":2691,"sourcePath":"06 newsletter/2026-week26.md","exportPath":"06-newsletter/2026-week26.html","showInTree":true,"treeOrder":1,"backlinks":[],"type":"markdown"},"06-newsletter/2026-week27.html":{"title":"2026-week27","icon":"","description":"Welcome back.\nI have decided to keep the rant i mentioned before, separate from this. when all you have is a hammer, everything is a nail paraphrased from memory, was a quote by Maslow. <img alt=\"HL_H8r_XsAAPVy1.jpg\" src=\"99-meta/attachments/hl_h8r_xsaapvy1.jpg\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 300px; max-width: 100%;\"><br><img alt=\"Pasted image 20260628004914.png\" src=\"99-meta/attachments/pasted-image-20260628004914.png\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 500px; max-width: 100%;\">\nI get that he's a millionaire and he doesn't have to worry about money being an issue, but it's still pretty surprising that someone so mainstream just randomly spirals into all of this.\nNot to mention him becoming so good at drawing in less than a year. <br><img alt=\"Pasted image 20260703124226.png\" src=\"99-meta/attachments/pasted-image-20260703124226.png\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 500px; max-width: 100%;\">Lord of the mysteries webnovel. I mean the writing is very visual. It's almost as if I'm watching a movie.\nAlmost anything I say about this is a spoiler.\nI have read about a 130 chapters or so in this week itself. I may need help.it was peak. pls watch it. a hypnotist leaves a guy in a state of daze and it makes his work life better(?)Coming on to movies, I watched this one because a friend of mine suggested this for its cinematography. It was the same friend who recommended office space.\nI'm gonna need a second rewatch the understand the story properly, I can write what I think happened but that's gonna be a spoiler. so. It will be included in the next week i think.Started playing undertale. Pacifist route. Stuck at undyne. <br><img alt=\"HH_D2nuXMAMzJXX.jpg\" src=\"99-meta/attachments/hh_d2nuxmamzjxx.jpg\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 200px; max-width: 100%;\">\nmore libertarian infighting (minarchism vs ancap)<br><img alt=\"Pasted image 20260629213158.png\" src=\"99-meta/attachments/pasted-image-20260629213158.png\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 500px; max-width: 100%;\">\nThe two choices.<br><img alt=\"HMPPlNzWQAAgZP2.jpg\" src=\"99-meta/attachments/hmpplnzwqaagzp2.jpg\" target=\"_self\"><br><a rel=\"noopener nofollow\" class=\"external-link is-unresolved\" href=\"https://mises.org/journal-libertarian-studies/marxist-and-austrian-class-analysis\" target=\"_self\">https://mises.org/journal-libertarian-studies/marxist-and-austrian-class-analysis</a>\nParallels between marxist and austrian class analysis.\nmarx blamed bourgeoisie, while austrian economists blame the non productive class.\nThe way the non productive class is defined is based on consent, rather than based on who owns the means of production, and \"steals the surplus value\"\nObviously the source I linked is kinda biased, but I still liked the parallels.\nMises institute is against intellectual property laws so every research paper or book over there is free, you could check this particular paper if you wish. Its 15 pages and 3 of them are just citations. <br><a rel=\"noopener nofollow\" class=\"external-link is-unresolved\" href=\"https://old.reddit.com/r/Polcompball/comments/1uc1rl1/polcompball_board_game_release_date_2606_2000_brt/\" target=\"_self\">https://old.reddit.com/r/Polcompball/comments/1uc1rl1/polcompball_board_game_release_date_2606_2000_brt/</a>\nThe Political Compass Board Game.\nI so want to play this. Finally reached 50kg in weight. I just hope it lasts. It's been so long since it had increased by even one kg. happened on 28th june.the yearbook thingy that i was working on has a few things left, but it is mostly done. I'm honestly pretty fond of it.Got sick for two days due to cold. back to my original weight. Fml.I have been sleeping a LOT lately. Exceeding 14 hours a day or so by now. ","aliases":[],"inlineTags":[],"frontmatterTags":[],"headers":[{"heading":"misc","level":1,"id":"misc_0"},{"heading":"PewDiePie","level":2,"id":"PewDiePie_0"},{"heading":"Media","level":1,"id":"Media_0"},{"heading":"lotm","level":2,"id":"lotm_0"},{"heading":"office space (1999)","level":2,"id":"office_space_(1999)_0"},{"heading":"Stay (2005)","level":2,"id":"Stay_(2005)_0"},{"heading":"Undertale","level":2,"id":"Undertale_0"},{"heading":"Political stuff","level":1,"id":"Political_stuff_0"},{"heading":"memes etc.","level":2,"id":"memes_etc._0"},{"heading":"marxist and austrian class analysis","level":2,"id":"marxist_and_austrian_class_analysis_0"},{"heading":"political compass board game","level":2,"id":"political_compass_board_game_0"},{"heading":"Life updates","level":1,"id":"Life_updates_0"}],"links":[],"author":"","coverImageURL":".","fullURL":"06-newsletter/2026-week27.html","pathToRoot":"..","attachments":["99-meta/attachments/hl_h8r_xsaapvy1.jpg","99-meta/attachments/pasted-image-20260628004914.png","99-meta/attachments/pasted-image-20260703124226.png","99-meta/attachments/hh_d2nuxmamzjxx.jpg","99-meta/attachments/pasted-image-20260629213158.png","99-meta/attachments/hmpplnzwqaagzp2.jpg"],"createdTime":1782584666987,"modifiedTime":1783277143273,"sourceSize":2911,"sourcePath":"06 newsletter/2026-week27.md","exportPath":"06-newsletter/2026-week27.html","showInTree":true,"treeOrder":2,"backlinks":[],"type":"markdown"},"06-newsletter/2026-week28.html":{"title":"2026-week28","icon":"","description":"Was possessed by the sloth demon. Did mostly nothing except laze around and read LoTM. And doomscrolled. My internship station finally responded. So more useless work. Yay. <img alt=\"HMK9gBMXwAAFbkx.jpg\" src=\"99-meta/attachments/hmk9gbmxwaafbkx.jpg\" target=\"_self\">","aliases"